\lim_{x \rightarrow 0} \int_0^T \frac{1}{\sqrt{\pi t}} \exp \left(-\frac{x^2}{t}-t\right) \left(1-\frac{t}{T} \right) \mbox{d}t
 \int_0^T \lim_{x \rightarrow 0}\frac{1}{\sqrt{\pi t}} \exp \left(-\frac{x^2}{t}-t\right) \left(1-\frac{t}{T} \right) \mbox{d}t=\\ \frac{1}{\sqrt{\pi t}} \exp \left(-t\right) \left(1-\frac{t}{T} \right) \mbox{d}t=\\ \exp^{-T}/\sqrt{\pi T} + (2 - 1/T) \mbox{erf}(\sqrt{T})
t\rightarrow 0
x>0
\delta_t(x)=\lim_{t \rightarrow 0} \frac{1}{\sqrt{\pi t}} \exp \left(-\frac{x^2}{t}\right)
